{
  "uid": "aegis-forecast-drift-volatility",
  "title": "AEGIS Forecast Drift — Volatility",
  "description": "Volatility drift family (governed weight 10%): rolling dispersion / oscillation / sign-change behavior via volatility_drift_score. Governed read-only V2 snapshot through datasource aegis-forecast-drift-csv (forecast_drift_signals.csv + forecast_drift_family_scores.csv + forecast_drift_runs.csv). Volatility is only PARTIALLY computable: 144 of 168 signals have a volatility_drift_score (coverage 85.7%); the 24 non-computable signals are governed by not_computable_reason = INSUFFICIENT_VERSIONS (the first two forecast versions of each key lack enough history). Governed auxiliary metrics (rolling_stddev, rolling_cov, rolling_mad, oscillation_count, sign_change_freq, volatility_class) live in the family-scores table and are surfaced in a dedicated profile panel keyed by forecast_key + forecast_version. The drift trend intentionally ignores the Forecast Version filter to preserve the full historical series.",
